Part I - FIFA22-Soccer¶

by Jamil Abdulai¶

Introduction¶

The main target for this analysis are real soccer players as well as soccer fanatics. Real soccer players will benefit the most from our analysis. If I was soccer player, I would be looking to learn which attribute of my self I can boost the most to not only improve my self as a player but to also improve my salary. I hope that our analysis could help players direct their workout regiment by helping understand which attributes are truly considered valuable in soccer and for a club. Soccer fanatics will also benefit from our analysis as it will help them better understand which characteristics they may want to look for when looking at potential trade prospects for their respective team.

The dataset is in a two part .csv files, 'players_fifa22.csv' and 'teams_fifa22.csv'. The intention is to analyze the 'players_fifa22.csv' file for this project. Access to dataset : https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/bryanb/fifa-player-stats-database

Insights:¶

  1. From the descriptive analysis of the dataset, the average wage in Euros is 8,973.53 out of 19,260 players. The minimum was 0 with a maximum of 350,0000 Euros weekly.Also, 75%f the players averages 8,000.00 Euros compared to a median of 3,000 Euros.

  2. With respect to the age, the oldest player is 54 years old whereas the youngest was 16 years of age. Furthermore, 75% of the players are 29 years compared to a median of 25 out of 19,260 players.

  3. Likely, the tallest players is 206cm compared to the shortest recorded as 155cm with a median and 75% recorded as 186cm and 181cm respectively.

  4. The player with the highest value in Euros is 194,000,000.00 compared to the lowest value of 0.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The above dataset was initially composed of 19260 rows and 90 columns prior to wrangling. Unwanted columns were dropped as well as null values to enhance the overall objective of the analysis. The data has both categorical and quantitative data which will absolutely enhance the visualization processes.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The primary focus will be on the characteristics of the players and their ability to either perform. Emphasis will be placed on what separates the best from the rest. Factors like age, nationality, overall, poential, club, value, wages, position, body type, work rate, international reputation, preferred foot, ball control and agility will be analyzed.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

Characteristics like wage, age, weight, height and weight will have massive implications on the analysis.

#Define all the labels for the visualization
def label(x,y,t):
    """
    Args:
      x(str): label of x-axis
      y(str): label of y-axis
      t(str): label of title
    
    Returns: 
      None
    """
    plt.xlabel(x)
    plt.ylabel(y)
    plt.title()

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

Quantitative Statistical Analysis of Data

  1. A histogram distribution of the growth of players were analyzed. From the analysis, the visualization is right skewed/ positive skewed which means that the peak of the graph lies to the left side of the center. On the right side of the graph, the frequencies of observations are lower than the frequencies of observations to the left side.
  2. Also, a histogram distribution of the potential of players was analyzed. From the analysis, the distribution is bell-shaped/normall dsitribution hence the mode, mean and median are all centrally aligned with most potential within the 70s.
  3. Furthermore, a visual histogram presentation of the ages indicated that, majority of the players are within the ages of 20-30 years.
  4. In addition, when the distribution of the weight-class was analyzed, it was adamant that the most players weighed between 70-80kg.
  5. Lastly, the visual distribution of the heights of the players reinterates that majority of them were bewteen 175-180cm.

Visualizations of categorical variables

  1. The top 10 nationalities of the players were analyzed with majority originating from England followed by Germany, Spain, France, Argentina and Brazil.
  2. Also, a graph of the Top 25 most popular clubs indicated that all the countries stemmed from the continent of Europe like Paris Saint-Germain, FC Barcelona, Real Madrid CF, Manchester City and Arsenal just to mention few.
  3. The analysis of the most preferred position show that majority of the players preferred CB-Center Back, ST-Striker, CAM-Central Attacking Midfielder, GK-Goalkeeper, RM-Right Midfield, CDM-Central Defensive Midfielder with the rest of the other positions not mostly favored by the players.
  4. Lastly, the analization of the preferred foot of players clearly indicates that more than 50% of the soccer players are predominantly right-footed

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

Upon analysis, I came across multiple columns with similar meaning or data like 'Name' and 'FullName' hence I deleted it.Also, the 'Positions' and 'BestPositions' columns provided similar information hence the Positions columns was eliminated.Columns like 'PhotoUrl', 'OnLoad', 'NationalPosition' and'NationalNumber' were all deleted because it was irrelevant for the anlysis. Lastly, the statiscal histogram distribution of growth took me aback after the plot due to majority of the players showing a '0' growth but after further investigation, I noticed it made sense because the comparison of the overall performance of those players with respect to previous yeay(YoY) were the same.

There are multiple soccer clubs across the globe. From the analysis, any soccer fanatic will attest to the fact that his/her club is among the top 30 clubs on the list. From the Real Madrid, FC Barcelona, Paris Saint-Germain, Manchester United, Manchester City, Arsenal, Chelsea and Tottenham Hotspur just to mention a few with all from Europe.

Heat Map of data¶

  1. Pace total have a negative correlation with weight and height
  2. Jumping has a positive correlation with jumping abilities
  3. Height and weight have negative correlation with acceleration and sprint
  4. Heading accuracy have a negative correlation with height and weight
  5. Potential have negative correlation with age.
  6. Penalties have positive correlation with finishing
